00:34:47,086 --> 00:34:49,216
And... rose fertilizer.

907
00:34:49,221 --> 00:34:52,721
Which also has nitrogen.

908
00:34:52,724 --> 00:34:55,034
So the rods were taken
from a garden.

909
00:34:55,027 --> 00:34:56,257
Exactly.

910
00:34:56,261 --> 00:34:57,661
Garden tools,

911
00:34:57,663 --> 00:34:59,803
lawn accessories...
Like flamingos.

912
00:34:59,798 --> 00:35:02,198
Well, yeah, I mean,
that's oddly specific,

913
00:35:02,201 --> 00:35:04,601
but, yeah,
flamingos...
Thank you. Thank you.

914
00:35:14,413 --> 00:35:16,283
Mr. Morningstar.

915
00:35:16,281 --> 00:35:18,421
Hello, murderer.

916
00:35:18,417 --> 00:35:20,247
Murderer?

917
00:35:20,252 --> 00:35:21,522
(door shuts)

918
00:35:21,520 --> 00:35:23,090
I don't...
I don't understand.

919
00:35:23,088 --> 00:35:26,088
Oh, Roberta, can we skip the
boring part where you deny it

920
00:35:26,091 --> 00:35:30,391
and just, uh... Let's get
to the good stuff, shall we?

921
00:35:30,395 --> 00:35:33,025
Does it help
if I call you Bobby B.?

922
00:35:33,031 --> 00:35:34,561
What are you talking about?

923
00:35:34,566 --> 00:35:36,796
Oh. Oh, it's very simple.

924
00:35:36,802 --> 00:35:38,542
You stole drugs
from the hospital

925
00:35:38,537 --> 00:35:39,797
and sold them to Amy Dodd,

926
00:35:39,805 --> 00:35:41,705
your biggest client,
who you met on set.

927
00:35:41,707 --> 00:35:44,437
You introduced Gillian
to Amy, got her the job.

928
00:35:44,443 --> 00:35:47,043
But then she helped Amy
get sober.

929
00:35:47,045 --> 00:35:49,145
You felt betrayed,
yadda yadda yadda,

930
00:35:49,148 --> 00:35:51,918
